        -:  185:/**
        -:  186: * \brief Performs a symbolic factorization on a panel of columns [jcol, jcol+w)
        -:  187: * 
        -:  188: * A supernode representative is the last column of a supernode.
        -:  189: * The nonzeros in U[*,j] are segments that end at supernodes representatives
        -:  190: * 
        -:  191: * The routine returns a list of the supernodal representatives 
        -:  192: * in topological order of the dfs that generates them. This list is 
        -:  193: * a superset of the topological order of each individual column within 
        -:  194: * the panel.
        -:  195: * The location of the first nonzero in each supernodal segment 
        -:  196: * (supernodal entry location) is also returned. Each column has 
        -:  197: * a separate list for this purpose. 
        -:  198: * 
        -:  199: * Two markers arrays are used for dfs :
        -:  200: *    marker[i] == jj, if i was visited during dfs of current column jj;
        -:  201: *    marker1[i] >= jcol, if i was visited by earlier columns in this panel; 
        -:  202: * 
        -:  203: * \param[in] m number of rows in the matrix
        -:  204: * \param[in] w Panel size
        -:  205: * \param[in] jcol Starting  column of the panel
        -:  206: * \param[in] A Input matrix in column-major storage
        -:  207: * \param[in] perm_r Row permutation
        -:  208: * \param[out] nseg Number of U segments
        -:  209: * \param[out] dense Accumulate the column vectors of the panel
        -:  210: * \param[out] panel_lsub Subscripts of the row in the panel 
        -:  211: * \param[out] segrep Segment representative i.e first nonzero row of each segment
        -:  212: * \param[out] repfnz First nonzero location in each row
        -:  213: * \param[out] xprune The pruned elimination tree
        -:  214: * \param[out] marker work vector
        -:  215: * \param  parent The elimination tree
        -:  216: * \param xplore work vector
        -:  217: * \param glu The global data structure
        -:  218: * 
        -:  219: */
        -:  220:
        -:  221:template <typename Scalar, typename StorageIndex>
    #####:  222:void SparseLUImpl<Scalar,StorageIndex>::panel_dfs(const Index m, const Index w, const Index jcol, MatrixType& A, IndexVector& perm_r, Index& nseg, ScalarVector& dense, IndexVector& panel_lsub, IndexVector& segrep, IndexVector& repfnz, IndexVector& xprune, IndexVector& marker, IndexVector& parent, IndexVector& xplore, GlobalLU_t& glu)
